WEBVTT

00:18.627 --> 00:20.846
[projector whirring]

00:20.890 --> 00:22.239
[woman] STAY AWAY FROM ME. LET GO.

00:22.283 --> 00:23.501
LET GO OF ME.

00:23.545 --> 00:25.851
[man] SAVE THE PHONY TEARS.

00:25.895 --> 00:29.551
JUST GET BACK.

00:29.594 --> 00:32.075
OH, YOU LITTLE FOOL. YOU JUST STAY AWAY
FROM ME.

00:32.119 --> 00:34.904
[gun fires, people screaming]

00:37.733 --> 00:40.170
[man] WE CAN'T GET INVOLVED
IN THIS.

00:40.214 --> 00:42.172
[lowered voice] HELLO, PATRICK.
HOW ARE YOU?

00:42.216 --> 00:44.783
[lowered voice] GOOD.

00:44.827 --> 00:45.915
SO WHAT DO YOU THINK?

00:45.958 --> 00:48.048
OH, IT'S A CLASSIC.

00:48.091 --> 00:49.049
YOU KNOW, IT JUST GETS

00:49.092 --> 00:51.181
BETTER AND BETTER
EVERY TIME.

00:51.225 --> 00:52.226
YES.

00:52.269 --> 00:55.359
WHAT DO YOU THINK
OF MY REQUEST?

00:55.403 --> 00:58.058
I DON'T THINK MUCH OF IT,
REALLY, PATRICK.

00:58.101 --> 00:59.972
REALLY, I DON'T.

01:00.016 --> 01:02.192
MEANING YOU CAN'T
ACCOMPLISH IT?

01:02.236 --> 01:04.107
ANY TASK CAN BE ACCOMPLISHED,

01:04.151 --> 01:07.893
AS LONG AS IT'S BROKEN DOWN
INTO MANAGEABLE PIECES.

01:07.937 --> 01:10.418
SO YOU'LL DO IT?

01:10.461 --> 01:13.638
LOOK, I KNOW
THAT I'M IN YOUR DEBT.

01:13.682 --> 01:16.989
OKAY, SO WE BOTH AGREE
THAT YOU OWE ME A FAVOR.

01:17.033 --> 01:18.904
YES, I DO.

01:18.948 --> 01:21.429
SO LET THIS BE
MY FAVOR TO YOU--

01:21.472 --> 01:24.127
LET IT GO--
THE WHOLE IDEA.

01:24.171 --> 01:26.521
IT'S JUST NOT WORTH IT.

01:30.046 --> 01:32.744
WELL, I FIND THIS
VERY INTERESTING.

01:32.788 --> 01:35.007
I'M PRESENTING YOU
WITH A CHALLENGE,

01:35.051 --> 01:37.445
AND YET
YOU'RE BACKING AWAY.

01:37.488 --> 01:40.622
IT'S VERY UNLIKE YOU,
MR. STILES.

01:40.665 --> 01:41.927
LOOK, IF YOU MUST KNOW,

01:41.971 --> 01:44.930
I'VE GROWN MILDLY ACCUSTOMED
TO YOU, PATRICK.

01:44.974 --> 01:47.324
YOU MAKE ME SIT UP
AND PAY ATTENTION.

01:47.368 --> 01:51.154
I'M VERY GLAD
YOU'RE AMUSED BY ME.

01:51.198 --> 01:54.244
BUT WHAT YOU'RE
PLANNING NOW, IT'S...

01:54.288 --> 01:56.681
WELL, IT'S
CERTAINLY DIFFERENT.

01:56.725 --> 01:58.118
YES, IT IS.

01:58.161 --> 02:02.426
IF I DO WHAT YOU'RE ASKING
OF ME AND YOU GET CAUGHT,

02:02.470 --> 02:04.428
YOU'RE GONNA SPEND
THE REST OF YOUR LIFE

02:04.472 --> 02:06.343
IN A FEDERAL PRISON.

02:06.387 --> 02:08.258
I'M WELL AWARE OF THAT.

02:08.302 --> 02:12.044
I JUST HAVE TO MAKE SURE
I DON'T GET CAUGHT.

02:12.088 --> 02:13.829
[sighs and chuckles]

02:13.872 --> 02:15.309
ALL RIGHT.

02:15.352 --> 02:21.793
WELL, IT'S BEEN A GREAT PLEASURE
KNOWING YOU, MR. JANE.

02:21.837 --> 02:23.360
GOOD LUCK.

02:23.404 --> 02:26.972
WELL, I-I USED
SOME PRETTY HARSH WORDS.

02:27.016 --> 02:28.148
I'M SORRY.

02:28.191 --> 02:29.192
THANK YOU.

02:29.236 --> 02:32.500
BUT NATURALLY, IF I'D KNOWN...

02:37.200 --> 02:40.943
[metal clanking]

02:45.339 --> 02:48.211
[machines whirring]

03:24.378 --> 03:25.770
[speaks inaudibly]

04:21.478 --> 04:23.698
[pounds truck]

05:01.736 --> 05:03.346
NEED A RIDE?

05:03.390 --> 05:05.174
YOU?

05:08.569 --> 05:11.528
♪♪♪

05:11.572 --> 05:13.443
--Captions by VITAC--

05:21.277 --> 05:25.150
HEY, COME ON. PLEASE.
JUST--JUST GET IN THE CAR.

05:25.194 --> 05:26.151
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

05:26.195 --> 05:27.414
WHY ARE YOU MAD AT ME?

05:27.457 --> 05:29.981
I-I DIDN'T FORCE YOU
TO ESCAPE FROM PRISON.

05:30.025 --> 05:32.506
NO, YOU JUST TRICKED ME
INTO IT.

05:37.032 --> 05:38.512
OH, COME ON.

05:38.555 --> 05:40.383
WAIT.

05:40.427 --> 05:42.342
YOU THOUGHT IT WAS RED JOHN
THAT GOT YOU OUT, DIDN'T YOU?

05:42.385 --> 05:43.865
YEAH.

05:43.908 --> 05:46.346
YEAH, WELL, IT WASN'T. I
DID. IGOT YOU OUT.

05:46.389 --> 05:47.999
HE WOULD HAVE LEFT YOU
IN THERE TO ROT.

05:48.043 --> 05:50.262
AND I TOOK A LOT OF RISKS
IN DOING IT.

05:50.306 --> 05:52.395
NOBODY EVER ACCUSED YOU
OF GOOD JUDGMENT.

05:52.439 --> 05:53.614
WELL, WHAT ABOUT YOU?

05:53.657 --> 05:55.006
YOU'RE THE ONE WALKING OFF
INTO THE DESERT

05:55.050 --> 05:57.487
10 MILES FROM A PRISON
YOU JUST BROKE OUT OF.

05:57.531 --> 05:59.271
I'M OFFERING YOU A RIDE.

05:59.315 --> 06:00.577
I'LL TAKE YOU
WHEREVER YOU WANNA GO.

06:00.621 --> 06:02.405
YOU CAN DUMP ME
AT ANY TIME.

06:04.233 --> 06:05.539
FINE.

06:08.759 --> 06:11.109
JANE, HOW MANY MESSAGES
DO I HAVE TO LEAVE YOU?

06:11.153 --> 06:12.633
CALL ME BACK.

06:16.463 --> 06:19.683
[speaking inaudibly]

06:19.727 --> 06:21.381
HOLD ON, TOM.
SHE JUST WALKED IN.

06:23.557 --> 06:25.036
NO.

06:25.080 --> 06:28.388
NO, DON'T INFORM
THE MARSHALS YET.

06:28.431 --> 06:32.435
I WANT TO BRING CBI
UP TO SPEED FIRST.

06:32.479 --> 06:33.958
I'LL CALL YOU BACK.

06:34.002 --> 06:35.699
WHAT'S GOING ON?

06:35.743 --> 06:38.049
HAVE YOU HEARD
ABOUT LORELEI MARTINS YET?

06:38.093 --> 06:39.616
NO.

06:39.660 --> 06:42.402
SHE ESCAPED FROM FEDERAL PRISON
THIS MORNING.

06:42.445 --> 06:47.232
YOUR MR. JANE WAS QUESTIONING
PRISON TRANSPORT DRIVERS.

06:47.276 --> 06:49.409
YES, BUT NO.

06:49.452 --> 06:50.932
HE WOULDN'T.

06:50.975 --> 06:53.238
HE WOULDN'T.

06:53.282 --> 06:55.893
HE WOULDN'T?

06:55.937 --> 06:57.765
WHERE IS HE NOW?

06:57.808 --> 07:00.811
I DON'T KNOW. I HAVEN'T HEARD
FROM HIM SINCE YESTERDAY.

07:00.855 --> 07:02.944
HE HASN'T ANSWERED
HIS PHONE.

07:02.987 --> 07:05.425
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN
HE DID THIS.

07:05.468 --> 07:08.340
IT WOULD MAKE IT
MUCH MORE LIKELY,

07:08.384 --> 07:09.472
WOULDN'T IT?

07:09.516 --> 07:11.474
WHY IS THIS
A HOMELAND SECURITY ISSUE?

07:11.518 --> 07:13.476
IT'S COMPLICATED.

07:13.520 --> 07:15.652
I MEAN, IF HE IS WITH HER,

07:15.696 --> 07:18.263
HE'S IN A LOT OF DANGER.

07:18.307 --> 07:20.004
YOU KNOW HIM
BETTER THAN ANYBODY.

07:20.048 --> 07:24.139
NOW IF HE DID DO THIS,
WHERE WOULD HE GO?

07:24.182 --> 07:26.446
ANY PLACE I COULD
POSSIBLY THINK OF

07:26.489 --> 07:30.580
IS WHERE HE WOULDN'T GO.

07:30.624 --> 07:32.364
UH, WOULD YOU EXCUSE ME
FOR A MINUTE?

07:32.408 --> 07:34.454
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

07:35.890 --> 07:38.762
HAS ANYONE SEEN JANE?

07:38.806 --> 07:39.763
NO.

07:39.807 --> 07:40.938
WE NEED TO FIND HIM
RIGHT NOW.

07:40.982 --> 07:42.462
PUT A B.O.L.O. OUT
ON HIS CAR.

07:42.505 --> 07:44.507
GRACE, CHO, I WANT YOU
TO GO TO HIS MOTEL ROOM.

07:44.551 --> 07:46.291
RIGS,
CALL HIS CELL PHONE COMPANY.

07:46.335 --> 07:47.945
GET GPS TRACKING ON HIS PHONE.

07:47.989 --> 07:49.512
WHAT'S GOING ON?

07:50.861 --> 07:53.516
LORELEI MARTINS ESCAPED
FROM PRISON THIS MORNING.

07:53.560 --> 07:55.605
WAS JANE INVOLVED?

07:55.649 --> 07:57.259
WE DON'T KNOW YET.

08:00.654 --> 08:02.786
BOB KIRKLAND,
HOMELAND SECURITY.

08:02.830 --> 08:04.179
HE'S LEADING THE SEARCH
TO FIND MARTINS.

08:04.222 --> 08:05.528
BOSS.

08:05.572 --> 08:07.617
SAC P.D. GOT A REPORT
OF AN ABANDONED BLUE CITROEN

08:07.661 --> 08:10.838
THIS MORNING. UH, PARKING LOT
AT 16th AND K STREET.

08:10.881 --> 08:12.622
TEXT IT TO ME.

08:12.666 --> 08:14.798
THIS ISN'T GONNA WORK.

08:14.842 --> 08:16.844
WELL, THAT'S OPTIMISTIC.

08:16.887 --> 08:20.630
I WON'T TELL YOU
WHO HE IS OR WHERE HE IS.

08:20.674 --> 08:22.414
GIVE IT TIME.

08:22.458 --> 08:24.939
NOT NOW. NOT EVER.

08:29.944 --> 08:31.511
[clicks]

08:31.554 --> 08:32.903
DOESN'T WORK.

08:32.947 --> 08:34.165
REALLY?

08:34.209 --> 08:36.690
I FIGURED THAT WHEN
NO SOUND CAME OUT OF IT.

08:36.733 --> 08:38.518
YES.

08:38.561 --> 08:39.649
[chuckles]

08:39.693 --> 08:43.523
CAN WE GO?

08:43.566 --> 08:45.307
TELL ME WHERE.

08:47.396 --> 08:51.313
THE OCEAN.
I WANNA SEE THE OCEAN.

08:56.579 --> 08:59.539
[police radio chatter]

09:02.585 --> 09:03.543
[car door closes]

09:05.153 --> 09:06.154
[horn honks]

09:16.251 --> 09:17.644
[cell phone beeps]

09:19.646 --> 09:21.038
HE WAS LEAVING
A TEXT MESSAGE.

09:21.082 --> 09:22.039
IT'S FOR YOU.

09:22.083 --> 09:24.259
"SOMEONE AFTER ME."

09:24.302 --> 09:27.218
HE WAS BEING FOLLOWED.

09:27.262 --> 09:28.959
LOOKS LIKE
HE'S BEEN ABDUCTED.

09:29.003 --> 09:31.919
JANE DOESN'T HAVE LORELEI.
LORELEI HAS JANE.

09:46.673 --> 09:49.110
OUR FUGITIVE
IS A KNOWN ASSOCIATE

09:49.153 --> 09:51.591
OF THE SERIAL KILLER
RED JOHN.

09:51.634 --> 09:54.158
SHE'S WANTED
FOR MURDER CONSPIRACY,

09:54.202 --> 09:56.639
KIDNAPPING,
AND WEAPONS VIOLATIONS.

09:56.683 --> 10:00.251
WE BELIEVE THAT MARTINS
AND UNKNOWN ACCOMPLICES

10:00.295 --> 10:04.125
ABDUCTED CBI CONSULTANT
PATRICK JANE.

10:04.168 --> 10:06.170
JANE LED A 6-MONTH
UNDERCOVER OPERATION

10:06.214 --> 10:07.911
THAT RESULTED
IN LORELEI'S ARREST.

10:07.955 --> 10:10.261
MARTINS MAY HAVE
KIDNAPPED HIM FOR PAYBACK

10:10.305 --> 10:11.306
OR TO TAKE HIM TO RED JOHN.

10:11.349 --> 10:12.655
EITHER WAY,
WE NEED TO FIND THEM.

10:12.699 --> 10:16.006
MARTINS IS
A SACRAMENTO GIRL.

10:16.050 --> 10:19.619
I WANT SYSTEMATIC SEARCHES
OF OLD RESIDENCES,

10:19.662 --> 10:21.142
OLD FRIENDS, OLD COWORKERS.

10:21.185 --> 10:23.274
YOU ALL HAVE
INFORMATION PACKETS.

10:23.318 --> 10:24.754
STUDY THEM,
AND WHEN YOU'RE DONE,

10:24.798 --> 10:27.365
CONTACT MYSELF OR AGENT KIRKLAND
FOR YOUR ASSIGNMENTS.

10:27.409 --> 10:28.628
THANK YOU.

10:28.671 --> 10:31.674
LET'S START
WITH LORELEI'S MOTHER.OKAY.

10:31.718 --> 10:34.416
[waves rolling]

11:02.749 --> 11:04.751
[Lorelei]
I WONDER WHERE THEY'REGOING.

11:24.553 --> 11:26.207
I'M GONNA MAKE A FIRE.

11:29.079 --> 11:31.821
SO, WHAT'S THIS ABOUT?

11:31.865 --> 11:32.996
[clears throat] YOUR DAUGHTER

11:33.040 --> 11:34.737
BROKE OUT OF PRISON
THIS MORNING.

11:34.781 --> 11:37.218
OH. OF COURSE.

11:37.261 --> 11:41.352
HAVE YOU HAD ANY CONTACT WITH--
WITH LORELEI RECENTLY?

11:41.396 --> 11:45.617
[chuckles] LORELEI HASN'T
CONTACTED ME IN YEARS.

11:45.661 --> 11:47.576
THANKFULLY.

11:47.619 --> 11:49.709
WHEN SHE DOES,

11:49.752 --> 11:52.581
IT'S ALWAYS TROUBLE.
ALWAYS.

11:52.624 --> 11:56.193
WE HAVE REASON TO BELIEVE THAT
LORELEI HAS TAKEN A HOSTAGE.

11:56.237 --> 11:57.847
HIS LIFE COULD BE IN DANGER.

11:57.891 --> 12:01.024
DO YOU HAVE ANY INFORMATION
THAT YOU COULD GIVE US

12:01.068 --> 12:03.244
ABOUT WHERE WE COULD FIND HER?

12:03.287 --> 12:06.769
ANY, UH, OLD FRIENDS?

12:06.813 --> 12:08.902
FAVORITE PLACES?

12:08.945 --> 12:11.861
NOPE. I DON'T HAVE
ANYTHING TO DO WITH HER,

12:11.905 --> 12:15.778
AND SHE DOESN'T HAVE
ANYTHING TO DO WITH ME.

12:15.822 --> 12:16.779
DO YOU HAVE ANY INSIGHT

12:16.823 --> 12:19.303
AS TO HOW
SHE BECAME THIS WAY?

12:19.347 --> 12:20.478
[chuckles]

12:20.522 --> 12:24.047
LORELEI ONLY EVER CARED
ABOUT LORELEI.

12:24.091 --> 12:25.919
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO
WITH A KID LIKE THAT?

12:25.962 --> 12:28.748
WELL, YOU DON'T FEEL
AT ALL RESPONSIBLE FOR HER?

12:28.791 --> 12:30.575
[chuckles]
NOW THERE'S A QUESTION

12:30.619 --> 12:32.752
FROM A WOMAN
WITHOUT CHILDREN.

12:36.712 --> 12:39.410
I'VE SATISFIED ALL MY DUTIES

12:39.454 --> 12:41.586
AND RESPONSIBILITIES
OF MOTHERHOOD.

12:41.630 --> 12:44.894
I MEAN, LOOK AROUND. LORELEI
GREW UP IN A BEAUTIFUL HOME.

12:44.938 --> 12:48.419
SHE COULD BE ANYTHING.

12:48.463 --> 12:50.247
IS THIS YOUR FATHER?

12:50.291 --> 12:52.075
[inhales deeply]

12:52.119 --> 12:55.818
THAT'S MY HUSBAND.
HE'S AWAY IN MUNICH.

12:55.862 --> 12:57.080
HE'S AWAY A LOT?

12:57.124 --> 12:58.821
YES.

12:58.865 --> 13:01.781
OH. FIGURES.

13:01.824 --> 13:03.434
I DON'T LIKE YOUR TONE.

13:03.478 --> 13:06.089
DANA, YOUR DAUGHTER
IS THE MISTRESS

13:06.133 --> 13:07.656
OF A PSYCHOPATHIC KILLER,

13:07.699 --> 13:09.266
YET YOU HAVE NO INFORMATION
TO GIVE US

13:09.310 --> 13:11.268
ABOUT HOW OR WHY
SHE GOT THAT WAY.

13:11.312 --> 13:13.793
FRANKLY, I DON'T CARE
IF YOU LIKE MY TONE.

13:13.836 --> 13:15.795
TO HELL WITH YOU, LADY.

13:15.838 --> 13:17.622
WHAT HAPPENED TO HER?

13:17.666 --> 13:21.844
GET OUT OF MY HOUSE.

13:21.888 --> 13:22.845
THANK YOU.

13:24.760 --> 13:27.763
[waves rolling]

13:42.996 --> 13:45.955
[crackling]

14:21.599 --> 14:21.643
[waves crashing]

15:33.019 --> 15:35.325
YOU SHOULD TRY IT.

15:35.369 --> 15:36.413
WATER'S LOVELY.

15:36.457 --> 15:38.807
EH.

15:41.549 --> 15:44.944
UH, QUICKLY--GO AND HIDE
YOURSELF BEHIND THOSE ROCKS.

15:58.566 --> 16:00.133
[sighs]

16:20.936 --> 16:21.893
HELLO, YOUNG MAN.

16:21.937 --> 16:22.894
HOW YOU DOING?

16:22.938 --> 16:24.592
[sniffs]

16:25.680 --> 16:28.117
[sniffs]

16:28.161 --> 16:30.032
WAS THAT YOUR CAMPFIRE?

16:30.076 --> 16:32.861
NO, OFFICER.

16:32.904 --> 16:35.907
I'M NOT AN OFFICER.
I'M A PARK RANGER.

16:35.951 --> 16:37.170
SO NO GUN, HUH?

16:37.213 --> 16:39.824
RIGHT.

16:39.868 --> 16:43.480
CAMPFIRES ARE ILLEGAL
ON THIS BEACH WITHOUT A PERMIT.

16:43.524 --> 16:47.006
WELL, IT... IT'S NOT MINE.

16:47.049 --> 16:50.226
ARE YOU OKAY, SIR?
YOU SEEM A LITTLE NERVOUS.

16:50.270 --> 16:51.880
NEVER BETTER.

16:56.363 --> 16:59.757
ARE YOU ALONE?

16:59.801 --> 17:03.500
UH, NO. SHE'S, UH...

17:03.544 --> 17:05.937
HI, OFFICER!
I'M OVER HERE!

17:05.981 --> 17:07.678
I'M SORRY. I CAN'T COME OUT!

17:07.722 --> 17:10.072
I DON'T HAVE ANY CLOTHES ON.

17:10.116 --> 17:14.859
YEAH, WELL, PUBLIC NUDITY'S
PROHIBITED ON STATE BEACHES.

17:14.903 --> 17:18.994
YES, UH, I'M SORRY!
IT WON'T HAPPEN AGAIN!

17:21.910 --> 17:23.738
PROMISE, IT--
IT WON'T HAPPEN AGAIN.

17:23.781 --> 17:26.045
SORRY, SIR.

17:28.134 --> 17:29.135
OKAY.

17:31.137 --> 17:32.877
YOU FOLKS
HAVE A NICE DAY.

17:32.921 --> 17:33.922
YEAH.

17:38.318 --> 17:39.319
NO CAMPFIRES.

17:52.027 --> 17:55.552
SO WHERE TO NOW?

17:55.596 --> 17:57.076
NORTH TO CANADA?

17:57.119 --> 18:00.557
SOUTH TO MEXICO?
I'M FLEXIBLE.

18:00.601 --> 18:03.082
I KNOW A PLACE
WHERE NO ONE WILL FIND US.

18:03.125 --> 18:07.129
TAKE THE I-60 EAST, BUT I
GOTTA CHANGE MY LOOK FIRST.

18:07.173 --> 18:09.392
FIND A CONVENIENCE STORE.

18:09.436 --> 18:11.133
I LIKE
THE TAKE-CHARGE ATTITUDE.

18:11.177 --> 18:12.134
NO, YOU DON'T.

18:12.178 --> 18:14.136
I DO.

18:14.180 --> 18:17.226
CLEARLY, YOU'VE TAKEN CARE
OF SOMEONE IN YOUR LIFE.

18:17.270 --> 18:20.229
MADE ALL THE DECISIONS.
ACTED THE ADULT.

18:20.273 --> 18:24.407
I'M GUESSING YOU HAD
A VAIN, SELFISH,

18:24.451 --> 18:26.583
AND CONTROLLING MOTHER.

18:26.627 --> 18:30.021
BUT YOU FOUND
THE STRENGTH TO PULL AWAY.

18:30.065 --> 18:33.677
DOES SHE
RESENT YOU FOR THAT?

18:33.721 --> 18:36.419
PATRICK, DO YOU REALLY
WANT TO GET TO KNOW ME?

18:36.463 --> 18:38.160
OF COURSE.

18:38.204 --> 18:40.119
GIVE THE ACT A REST.

18:40.162 --> 18:41.859
WHAT? I-I WASN'T...

18:41.903 --> 18:43.165
YES, YOU WERE.

18:45.820 --> 18:48.953
OKAY.

18:48.997 --> 18:50.390
I KNEW IT.

18:50.433 --> 18:53.132
SOON AS I HEARD THAT KIDNAPPING
REPORT ON MY RADIO.

18:53.175 --> 18:55.612
I CALLED IT IN.

18:55.656 --> 18:59.660
THIS IS THE YOUNG MAN
I TALKED TO.

18:59.703 --> 19:00.965
WAS THERE A WOMAN
WITH HIM?

19:01.009 --> 19:02.358
YES, THERE MOST CERTAINLY WAS.

19:02.402 --> 19:05.622
ONLY I DIDN'T SEE HER
ON ACCOUNT OF SHE WAS NAKED.

19:05.666 --> 19:07.885
AT LEAST THAT WHAT
SHE SAID.

19:07.929 --> 19:10.149
SHE WAS BEHIND THAT ROCK THERE
WHERE SHE WAS CHANGING.

19:10.192 --> 19:13.456
THE YOUNG MAN
GOT KIND OF JUMPY.UH-HUH.

19:13.500 --> 19:15.502
ASKED ME IF I HAD A GUN.

19:22.117 --> 19:24.075
SHE PROBABLY HAD A GUN
ON YOU THE WHOLE TIME.

19:24.119 --> 19:26.165
THAT'S WHAT I FIGURED.

19:26.208 --> 19:28.993
AND IF HE SAID ONE WRONG WORD
OR TRIED TO RUN--BAM.

19:29.037 --> 19:31.170
I MEAN, SHE WOULD HAVE
SHOT US BOTH DEAD.

19:31.213 --> 19:34.085
I'M JUST THANKFUL
HE KEPT HIS HEAD.

19:34.129 --> 19:36.305
HAPPEN TO SEE WHAT KIND
OF CAR THEY WERE DRIVING?

19:36.349 --> 19:38.916
YES, SIR. THERE WAS
ONLY ONE CAR ON THE BLUFF.

19:38.960 --> 19:42.572
A DARK BLUE 1990s
DYNASTY SEDAN.

19:46.533 --> 19:47.969
[gears shift]

19:52.756 --> 19:53.757
STAY LOW.

20:02.244 --> 20:05.334
[wind chimes tinkling]

20:05.378 --> 20:08.337
[Wylie & the Wild West's
"Without You" playing]

20:08.381 --> 20:10.383
[indistinct conversations,
laughter]

20:10.426 --> 20:13.168
[cash register beeps]

20:16.432 --> 20:21.872
♪ ON AN ISLAND ALL ALONE

20:21.916 --> 20:27.269
♪ A THOUSAND MILES
AWAY FROM HOME ♪

20:27.313 --> 20:30.054
[wind chimes tinkling]

20:30.098 --> 20:33.188
♪ ...WITHOUT YOU

20:37.801 --> 20:43.285
♪ SURROUNDED BY
AN ENDLESS SEA ♪

20:43.329 --> 20:45.113
♪ NOT A SOUL...

20:55.341 --> 21:01.999
♪♪♪

21:02.043 --> 21:07.918
♪ CAN MAKE ME FEEL
THE WAY YOU DO ♪

21:07.962 --> 21:11.748
♪ YOU'RE THE ROCK
I BUILD UPON ♪

21:11.792 --> 21:18.451
♪ YOU GIVE ME HOPE
AND KEEP ME STRONG ♪

21:18.494 --> 21:23.456
♪ THERE'S A PLACE
WHERE THE SUN WON'T SHINE ♪

21:23.499 --> 21:29.984
♪ WHERE BROKEN HEARTS
DON'T MEND WITH TIME ♪

21:30.027 --> 21:32.160
[clears throat] THANK YOU.

21:32.203 --> 21:35.163
[mutters indistinctly]

21:41.387 --> 21:44.346
[wind chimes tinkling]

21:50.700 --> 21:53.181
[whistles]

22:04.192 --> 22:05.454
SCARED YOU, DIDN'T I?

22:05.498 --> 22:07.543
NO.

22:07.587 --> 22:09.458
SAW SOME COPS. SPOOKED ME.[door alert chimes]

22:09.502 --> 22:11.547
[door closes]WELL, I'M GLAD
I LEFT YOU THE KEYS.

22:11.591 --> 22:14.463
YOU'RE GONNA BE
A FRENCH HONEY BLONDE.

22:14.507 --> 22:16.247
HOW'S THAT SOUND?SURE.

22:16.291 --> 22:18.162
DID YOU GET SNACKS?[engine starts]

22:18.206 --> 22:19.338
SURE DID.[shifts gears]

22:19.381 --> 22:20.426
[gravel crunches]

22:24.517 --> 22:25.561
[sighs]

22:27.433 --> 22:31.654
I HAVE SOMETHING TO SAY.

22:31.698 --> 22:34.875
COME IN. SIT DOWN, DANA.

22:37.921 --> 22:40.271
WHAT'S GOING ON?

22:44.537 --> 22:46.495
[exhales]

22:46.539 --> 22:50.107
COULDN'T SLEEP LAST NIGHT.
[chuckles]

22:50.151 --> 22:52.371
[inhales deeply]

22:52.414 --> 22:55.678
[exhales] HMM.

22:55.722 --> 22:59.247
MY HUSBAND MUSTN'T KNOW.

23:01.467 --> 23:03.382
MUSTN'T KNOW WHAT?

23:05.993 --> 23:07.908
[clears throat]

23:10.737 --> 23:12.303
[exhales]

23:12.347 --> 23:15.785
I SOLD LORELEI'S SISTER.

23:15.829 --> 23:17.091
SISTER?

23:17.134 --> 23:19.615
I DON'T REMEMBER READING
ANYTHING ABOUT A SISTER

23:19.659 --> 23:21.138
IN LORELEI'S FILE.

23:21.182 --> 23:24.925
[voice breaking]
BECAUSE I SOLD HER.

23:24.968 --> 23:29.146
ALL RIGHT, YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO HELP ME OUT HERE, DANA.

23:29.190 --> 23:33.542
30 YEARS AGO, I DIDN'T HAVE
THE MONEY TO RAISE 2 GIRLS.

23:33.586 --> 23:35.239
[inhales deeply]

23:35.283 --> 23:37.633
[whispers]
I HAD SUBSTANCE ISSUES.

23:40.331 --> 23:42.333
GO ON.

23:42.377 --> 23:45.424
SO AFTER... [clears throat]

23:45.467 --> 23:47.948
THEIR DAD LEFT...

23:47.991 --> 23:50.559
[inhales deeply]

23:50.603 --> 23:53.170
I JUST STOPPED FUNCTIONING,
YOU KNOW?

23:53.214 --> 23:59.481
AND, UM, LORELEI--
SHE WAS 5.

23:59.525 --> 24:04.355
AND SHE HELD ME UP,
YOU KNOW?

24:04.399 --> 24:09.273
BUT... [cries]

24:09.317 --> 24:14.453
MIRANDA--
THAT WAS HER NAME...

24:14.496 --> 24:16.629
SHE WAS 2.

24:16.672 --> 24:20.589
I MEAN, WHAT WAS I GONNA DO
WITH A 2-YEAR-OLD?

24:20.633 --> 24:22.504
WHAT DID YOU DO?

24:22.548 --> 24:24.767
WELL, I KNEW...

24:24.811 --> 24:27.466
I KNEW THIS RICH...
[clears throat] FOREIGN COUPLE,

24:27.509 --> 24:31.295
WHO... [sniffles]
CHILDLESS.

24:31.339 --> 24:34.385
SO WE MADE A DEAL UNDER
THE TABLE. [clears throat]

24:34.429 --> 24:36.605
WHY DIDN'T
THEY JUST ADOPT HER?

24:36.649 --> 24:39.826
WE ALL WANTED WHAT WE WANTED,
SO WE JUST GOT IT DONE.

24:39.869 --> 24:42.611
WHAT DID YOU TELL LORELEI?

24:42.655 --> 24:45.527
I TOLD HER...

24:47.529 --> 24:49.792
I TOLD HER ALL KINDS
OF STUFF.

24:49.836 --> 24:52.491
I... [sniffles]

24:52.534 --> 24:56.277
AND SHE NEVER FORGAVE ME.

24:58.192 --> 25:00.499
[sniffles]

25:00.542 --> 25:02.631
I DIDN'T REALIZE IT
AT THE TIME,

25:02.675 --> 25:07.027
BUT... THAT DAY...

25:07.070 --> 25:10.073
I LOST TWO DAUGHTERS.

25:10.117 --> 25:12.206
NOT ONE.

25:15.731 --> 25:23.173
WANT ME
TO GET YOU A TISSUE?

25:24.305 --> 25:27.308
[children shouting playfully]

25:36.056 --> 25:37.710
[child laughs]

25:53.943 --> 25:56.293
HEY THERE.

25:56.337 --> 25:58.295
LOOKING FOR A ROOM.

25:58.339 --> 26:00.602
PLACE TO REST
MY WEARY BONES.

26:00.646 --> 26:03.039
BEEN ON THE ROAD
SINCE NEW MEXICO.

26:03.083 --> 26:05.607
IT'S $48 CASH,
$52 CREDIT.

26:05.651 --> 26:07.043
OOP. I'LL BE PAYING CASH.

26:07.087 --> 26:11.221
OKAY.

26:11.265 --> 26:14.224
YOU DON'T HAPPEN TO
HAVE ONE WITHOUT A TELEVISION?

26:14.268 --> 26:19.621
UH, TV's BUSTED IN 13.
NO DISCOUNT.

26:19.665 --> 26:21.754
OKAY.

26:21.797 --> 26:25.584
[children continue shouting,
ball bouncing]

26:27.629 --> 26:28.587
[bell dings]

26:31.459 --> 26:32.591
HAVE A NICE DAY.

26:32.634 --> 26:33.635
MM-HMM.

26:33.679 --> 26:36.595
WE TRIED TO HAVE
OUR OWN CHILDREN.

26:36.638 --> 26:37.726
I COULD NOT.

26:37.770 --> 26:40.337
WHY DIDN'T YOU
JUST ADOPT LEGALLY?

26:40.381 --> 26:44.080
WELL, I WAS ON WORK VISA
FROM ROMANIA.

26:44.124 --> 26:47.257
AND WE COULD NOT ADOPT
UNTIL WE WERE CITIZENS,

26:47.301 --> 26:49.259
AND THAT TAKES YEARS.

26:49.303 --> 26:51.653
MR. KIRKLAND,
THIS IS MARTA AND VIRGIL ROMAN.

26:51.697 --> 26:56.092
THEY'RE JUST TELLING ME HOW THEY
CAME TO BUY MIRANDA MARTINS.

26:56.136 --> 26:58.486
YOU HAD TO SEE HER.

26:58.529 --> 27:01.663
SHE WAS IN
A BAD SITUATION.

27:01.707 --> 27:05.014
VIRGIL AND I KNEW WE COULD
GIVE HER A LIFE

27:05.058 --> 27:08.496
FULL OF LOVE
AND OPPORTUNITY.

27:08.539 --> 27:12.761
BUT SHE TURNED OUT TO BE
A VERY TROUBLED GIRL.

27:12.805 --> 27:16.199
VERY UNHAPPY.

27:16.243 --> 27:18.375
SO WHEN SHE WAS
IN HIGH SCHOOL,

27:18.419 --> 27:20.551
WE SENT HER
TO A THERAPIST,

27:20.595 --> 27:23.685
AND SHE REMEMBERED
A LOT OF THINGS

27:23.729 --> 27:27.776
WE THOUGHT
SHE HAD FORGOTTEN.

27:27.820 --> 27:28.777
HER MOTHER?

27:28.821 --> 27:31.780
NO.

27:31.824 --> 27:33.695
SHE REMEMBERED
ONLY ONE NAME--

27:33.739 --> 27:36.698
LORELEI.

27:36.742 --> 27:38.961
OF COURSE, WE FOUND
HER SISTER LORELEI

27:39.005 --> 27:40.528
AND REUNITED THEM.

27:40.571 --> 27:46.055
THE SISTERS WERE SO HAPPY,
AND THEY WERE SO CLOSE.

27:46.099 --> 27:51.495
YOU'VE NEVER SEEN
TWO SISTERS WHO WERE CLOSER.

27:51.539 --> 27:54.673
WHERE IS MIRANDA NOW?
WE NEED TO TALK TO HER.

27:54.716 --> 27:58.677
SHE... SHE WAS MURDERED.

27:58.720 --> 27:59.939
SHE'S DEAD.

28:10.732 --> 28:13.604
THANKS FOR THE DRESS.

28:13.648 --> 28:18.261
OH, IT'S MY PLEASURE.

28:18.305 --> 28:19.828
SO, LISTEN, UH...

28:19.872 --> 28:21.134
[clears throat]

28:22.788 --> 28:25.834
YOU GONNA TELL ME
WHERE WE'RE GOING?

28:25.878 --> 28:29.359
TO A CABIN MY SISTER AND I
USED TO GO TO.

28:29.403 --> 28:30.621
YOU HAVE A SISTER?

28:30.665 --> 28:31.971
I DID.

28:34.060 --> 28:35.844
I'M SORRY.

28:35.888 --> 28:38.455
DON'T BE.

28:38.499 --> 28:41.894
HER DEATH WAS A GIFT,
SORT OF.

28:41.937 --> 28:43.852
YOU WANT
TO EXPLAIN THAT?

28:43.896 --> 28:46.855
YOU WOULDN'T UNDERSTAND.

28:46.899 --> 28:49.075
WELL, YOU COULD TRY ME.

28:49.118 --> 28:52.426
I MEAN, I-I'D LIKE
TO UNDERSTAND.

28:52.469 --> 28:56.778
IN CASE YOU HAVEN'T NOTICED,
HEALING IS NOT MY STRONG SUIT.

28:56.822 --> 29:01.043
LOSING MY SISTER BROUGHT ME
INTO MY FULL REALITY.

29:01.087 --> 29:05.787
I FACED MY DEEPEST FEAR.

29:05.831 --> 29:09.922
I HAVE COMPLETE AWARENESS.

29:09.965 --> 29:12.576
NOTHING CAN HURT ME.

29:12.620 --> 29:15.754
THAT'S NONSENSE.
BELIEVE ME.

29:15.797 --> 29:18.104
THINGS CAN HURT YOU.

29:19.801 --> 29:21.150
TRY ME.[bottle cap fizzes]

29:21.194 --> 29:23.152
[cap clatters]

29:23.196 --> 29:25.938
MM. THIS BEER IS WARM.

29:25.981 --> 29:28.288
[bottle clatters]

29:28.331 --> 29:29.811
I'LL GET SOME ICE.

29:37.950 --> 29:40.691
MIRANDA WAS BEAUTIFUL,
LIKE HER SISTER.

29:40.735 --> 29:43.825
WHAT DOES THE CORONER'S REPORT
SAY ABOUT THE CAUSE OF DEATH?

29:43.869 --> 29:44.913
HEATSTROKE.

29:44.957 --> 29:46.480
AFTER SHE WAS RAPED,

29:46.523 --> 29:50.832
SHE WAS LEFT CHAINED
INSIDE OF AN EMPTY WAREHOUSE.

29:50.876 --> 29:53.835
DAYTIME TEMPERATURES
REACHED 120 DEGREES INSIDE.

29:53.879 --> 29:58.100
CORONER FIGURES
SHE LASTED ABOUT TWO DAYS.

29:58.144 --> 30:00.494
AND THEY NEVER FOUND
THE KILLER?

30:00.537 --> 30:01.930
THE CASE IS STILL OPEN.

30:01.974 --> 30:06.805
THERE'S NO TRACE EVIDENCE,
NO WITNESSES. JUST THIS.

30:06.848 --> 30:09.459
[cell phone chimes]

30:09.503 --> 30:10.460
[beep]

30:10.504 --> 30:12.985
HELLO?[Jane] Hey, Lisbon.

30:13.028 --> 30:14.856
I NEED YOUR HELP.

30:14.900 --> 30:17.032
[lowered voice] I NEED
TO TAKE THIS. COULD YOU...

30:17.076 --> 30:20.122
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

30:20.166 --> 30:22.821
[stations change,
static crackles]

30:22.864 --> 30:28.391
[Bing Crosby] ♪ AND THIS
REFRAIN WAS HER SONG ♪

30:28.435 --> 30:33.657
♪ RED SAILS IN THE SUNSET

30:33.701 --> 30:35.964
♪ WAY OUT ON THE SEA

30:36.008 --> 30:38.488
JANE, WHAT'S GOING ON?
HAVE YOU BEEN KIDNAPPED?

30:38.532 --> 30:40.316
YES. I'M IN FEAR
OF MY LIFE.

30:40.360 --> 30:41.709
I CAN'T TALK LONG.

30:41.752 --> 30:43.842
DID YOU KNOW LORELEI
HAD A SISTER?

30:43.885 --> 30:46.148
YES. MIRANDA.
HER MOTHER GAVE HER UP.

30:46.192 --> 30:47.715
WHERE ARE YOU?

30:47.758 --> 30:48.890
If she catches me on the phone,

30:48.934 --> 30:49.891
SHE'LL KILL ME.

30:49.935 --> 30:51.980
WHAT HAPPENED TO MIRANDA?

30:52.024 --> 30:53.373
SHE WAS MURDERED.

30:53.416 --> 30:55.723
ABDUCTED, RAPED, AND LEFT
FOR DEAD FIVE YEARS AGO.

30:55.766 --> 30:57.333
Who did it?THEY DON'T KNOW.

30:57.377 --> 30:58.552
THEY DON'T EVEN
HAVE A SUSPECT.

30:58.595 --> 30:59.945
But listen to this--

30:59.988 --> 31:02.338
the police kept back
a key detail from the public.

31:02.382 --> 31:03.687
Before Miranda died,

31:03.731 --> 31:06.212
SHE CARVED A MESSAGE
INTO THE WAREHOUSE FLOOR.

31:06.255 --> 31:07.778
WHAT'D IT SAY?

31:07.822 --> 31:09.998
I'M LOOKING AT
THE CRIME SCENE PHOTO NOW.

31:10.042 --> 31:11.086
IT SAYS "ROY."

31:14.785 --> 31:16.004
I NEED A COPY OF THAT PHOTO.

31:16.048 --> 31:21.444
UH, LISBON, YEAH. FAX IT
TO ME AT THIS NUMBER...

31:21.488 --> 31:23.098
[female announcer on radio]
I'M KATIE RILEY,

31:23.142 --> 31:25.927
AND I'LL BE BACK WITH MORE
OF YOUR FAVORITE MELLOW BLENDS

31:25.971 --> 31:27.624
RIGHT AFTER THE NEWS.

31:27.668 --> 31:28.930
[male announcer]
STATE AND FEDERAL AUTHORITIES

31:28.974 --> 31:30.801
HAVE INTENSIFIED THE SEARCH

31:30.845 --> 31:33.369
FOR A SACRAMENTO WOMAN,
LORELEI MARTINS.

31:33.413 --> 31:35.371
JANE, JUST TELL ME
WHERE YOU ARE.

31:35.415 --> 31:36.459
WE CAN HELP YOU.

31:36.503 --> 31:37.939
JUST FAX IT TO ME.

31:37.983 --> 31:40.202
I GOTTA GO. GOTTA GO.

31:40.246 --> 31:41.595
[receiver clatters]

31:46.687 --> 31:49.690
[fax machine whirring]

31:51.083 --> 31:54.608
ACCORDING TO POLICE,
MARTINS IS HOLDING A HOSTAGE,

31:54.651 --> 31:57.785
PATRICK JANE. YESTERDAY,
CBI CONSULTANT JANE'S CAR

31:57.828 --> 31:59.961
WAS FOUND ABANDONED
BY THE SIDE OF THE ROAD.

32:00.005 --> 32:01.876
[fax machine whirring]

32:03.008 --> 32:06.011
[whirring]

32:14.019 --> 32:15.716
EVERYTHING OKAY?

32:17.109 --> 32:19.459
JANE JUST CALLED ME.

32:30.818 --> 32:31.819
[door squeaks]

32:37.825 --> 32:41.089
YOU LIE!AAH!

32:41.133 --> 32:42.786
[grunts]

32:42.830 --> 32:52.361
LIAR!

32:53.145 --> 32:54.102
FILTHY LIAR! KIDNAPPED?!

32:54.146 --> 32:54.537
PLEASE...HOW DARE YOU?! YOU LIED!

32:54.581 --> 32:56.670
[panting]

32:56.713 --> 33:00.282
I DIDN'T LIE. I JUST
DIDN'T TELL YOU EVERYTHING.

33:00.326 --> 33:02.458
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME?

33:02.502 --> 33:04.808
I HAD TO PROTECT MYSELF.

33:04.852 --> 33:06.723
[grunts]

33:06.767 --> 33:07.898
AAH!

33:07.942 --> 33:08.899
OH!

33:08.943 --> 33:12.599
PLEASE. JUST STOP.
[panting]

33:17.082 --> 33:19.693
YOU HAD ME GOING, PATRICK.

33:19.736 --> 33:21.695
[panting]

33:26.526 --> 33:29.833
FOR A SECOND THERE,
I ALMOST TRUSTED YOU.

33:29.877 --> 33:32.010
YOU SHOULD.
YOU SHOULD TRUST ME.

33:32.053 --> 33:35.665
OH, STOP!
JUST STOP PLAYING THE ROLE.

33:35.709 --> 33:37.667
YES, I PLAY A ROLE,
BUT NOT WITH YOU.

33:37.711 --> 33:39.408
I'M BEING HONEST WITH YOU.LIES ON LIES!

33:39.452 --> 33:41.671
LORELEI, LISTEN TO ME.
YOU HAVE TO LISTEN TO ME.

33:41.715 --> 33:46.024
YOUR BUDDY RED JOHN--
HE KILLED YOUR SISTER.

33:46.067 --> 33:49.070
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?YOUR SISTER MIRANDA.

33:49.114 --> 33:52.160
SHE WROTE A NAME ON THE FLOOR
OF THE WAREHOUSE WHERE SHE DIED.

33:52.204 --> 33:54.162
THE NAME OF THE MAN
WHO RAPED AND KILLED HER.

33:54.206 --> 33:56.034
IT WAS NEVER RELEASED
TO THE PUBLIC.

33:56.077 --> 33:57.948
YOU'RE MAKING THAT UP.NO.

33:57.992 --> 34:00.560
THIS IS A CRIME SCENE PHOTO
OF YOUR SISTER'S MURDER.

34:05.086 --> 34:06.870
"ROY."

34:06.914 --> 34:07.871
YES, ROY.

34:07.915 --> 34:11.571
WE BOTH KNOW
WHO USES THAT ALIAS.

34:11.614 --> 34:14.530
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

34:14.574 --> 34:17.446
WHERE DID YOU GET THIS?IT DOESN'T MATTER.

34:17.490 --> 34:19.709
RED JOHN RAPED
AND KILLED YOUR SISTER.

34:19.753 --> 34:23.061
NO.HE MADE YOU A VICTIM
SO THAT HE COULD RESCUE YOU.

34:23.104 --> 34:25.237
NO.HE PREYED ON YOUR PAIN.

34:25.280 --> 34:27.108
NO, IT'S NOT TRUE.YES. YOU DON'T WANT IT
TO BE TRUE,

34:27.152 --> 34:28.936
BUT IT'S TRUE, AND YOU CAN
FEEL THAT IT'S TRUE.

34:28.979 --> 34:30.677
JUST STOP!

34:32.853 --> 34:35.116
GOD, YOU'RE JUST
LIKE HIM, YOU KNOW THAT?

34:35.160 --> 34:37.814
RELENTLESS MANIPULATION.I AM NOTHING LIKE HIM.

34:37.858 --> 34:39.903
HOW WOULD YOU KNOW?

34:39.947 --> 34:41.905
I KNOW.

34:41.949 --> 34:45.083
I ONLY WONDER WHY THE TWO OF YOU
DIDN'T BECOME LIFELONG FRIENDS

34:45.126 --> 34:47.433
THE MOMENT YOU SHOOK HANDS.

34:49.261 --> 34:51.089
[ice clatters]

34:51.132 --> 34:53.091
[door slams]WAIT!

34:55.528 --> 34:57.138
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

34:57.182 --> 34:58.748
WE STILL GOING
TO THE CABIN?

34:58.792 --> 35:01.142
THAT'S WHERE I'M GOING.
YOU CAN GO WHERE YOU LIKE.

35:14.155 --> 35:16.114
WE TRACED JANE'S CALL
TO A TRUCK STOP MOTEL

35:16.157 --> 35:18.768
ON ROUTE 99
JUST NORTH OF CHICO.RIGHT HERE.

35:18.812 --> 35:20.118
THE FUGITIVE AND HER HOSTAGE
WERE GONE

35:20.161 --> 35:22.337
BY THE TIME
DEPUTIES GOT TO THE MOTEL.

35:22.381 --> 35:25.253
[Buffalo Springfield]
♪ STEP OUT OF LINE

35:25.297 --> 35:28.996
♪ THE MAN COME
AND TAKE YOU AWAY ♪

35:29.039 --> 35:32.260
♪ YOU BETTER STOP,
HEY, WHAT'S THAT SOUND? ♪

35:32.304 --> 35:34.132
♪ EVERYBODY LOOK WHAT'S GOING

35:34.175 --> 35:36.960
♪ YOU BETTER STOP,
HEY, WHAT'S THAT SOUND? ♪

35:37.004 --> 35:39.137
[Kirkland]
THEY WERE MOVING NORTH.

35:39.180 --> 35:41.139
LET'S ASSUME THEY STILL ARE.
WHERE ARE THEY GOING?

35:41.182 --> 35:42.618
WELL, IF THEY TAKE THE 97 NORTH,

35:42.662 --> 35:43.967
THEY'LL HIT
THE BUTTER VALLEY AIRPORT.

35:44.011 --> 35:46.796
ONE RUNWAY. PUBLIC USE.
FIVE TAKEOFFS A DAY.

35:46.840 --> 35:49.190
THEY MIGHT GO FOR A PLANE.
OKAY, LOCK IT DOWN. WHAT ELSE?

35:49.234 --> 35:50.365
I'VE BEEN GOING
THROUGH FINANCIAL RECORDS

35:50.409 --> 35:51.627
FOR LORELEI'S SISTER.

35:51.671 --> 35:53.151
SHE OWNED A CABIN IN THE SIERRAS

35:53.194 --> 35:54.804
ABOUT 200 MILES NORTH
OF THAT MOTEL.

35:54.848 --> 35:57.894
FROM WHAT I CAN SEE, THE CABIN
WAS NEVER SOLD AFTER HER DEATH.

35:57.938 --> 36:00.288
AN ANONYMOUS THIRD PARTY HAS
BEEN PAYING THE TAXES ON IT.

36:00.332 --> 36:01.289
RED JOHN?[Kirkland] CALL TACTICAL.

36:01.333 --> 36:03.509
I WANT A CHOPPER HERE IN TEN.

36:05.728 --> 36:08.514
IT'S JUST UP AHEAD,
AT THE END OF THE ROAD.

36:18.959 --> 36:20.526
[shifts gears]

36:25.052 --> 36:28.011
YOU GO AHEAD.
I'LL GET THE STUFF.

36:28.055 --> 36:29.056
OKAY.

36:42.896 --> 36:45.159
THE KEY
IS UNDER THE FLOWER POT.

37:30.335 --> 37:32.641
WELCOME.[gasps]

37:32.685 --> 37:35.253
WELL, IT'S A NICE PLACE.

37:35.296 --> 37:38.560
YEAH.

37:38.604 --> 37:40.910
BELONGED TO MY SISTER.

37:40.954 --> 37:43.870
WE USED TO COME HERE
TO FORGET ABOUT THE WORLD.

37:46.220 --> 37:47.265
[sighs]

37:47.308 --> 37:48.483
IT'S SAFE.

37:53.009 --> 37:56.012
RED JOHN DIDN'T
KILL HER, PATRICK.

37:56.056 --> 37:59.189
YOU'LL NEVER CONVINCE ME
THAT HE DID.

37:59.233 --> 38:03.019
I'D KILL FOR
A CUP OF TEA RIGHT NOW.

38:03.063 --> 38:07.589
I CAN MAKE YOU ONE.

38:07.633 --> 38:10.592
I'D LIKE THAT.

38:10.636 --> 38:12.420
BUT WE CAN'T STAY HERE.

38:12.464 --> 38:13.943
WHY NOT?

38:13.987 --> 38:16.598
IF MIRANDA BOUGHT THIS PLACE,
THE POLICE'LL FIND IT.

38:16.642 --> 38:19.514
THEY'RE PROBABLY
ON THEIR WAY HERE RIGHT NOW.

38:19.558 --> 38:21.516
THEN WE HAVE TO GO.NO, YOU HAVE TO GO.

38:21.560 --> 38:23.605
I'LL STAY.
